<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17001] &lt;threads&gt; behavior change in Camel 3</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17001</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello everyone,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just noticed a behavior change when using the &amp;lt;threads&amp;gt; tag in Camel 3.x compared to Camel 2.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code snippet is the following&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &amp;lt;route&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;from uri=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;timer:foo?repeatCount=1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;log message=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Before threads&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;threads poolSize=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;5&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
            &amp;lt;log message=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;In threads&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;/threads&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;log message=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;After threads&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Camel 2.x, the &quot;In threads&quot; message is displayed which is not the case in 3.x. This is due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/commit/2724f9aa30025752dcea85b1f41aeaae6ca4c989&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this commit&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In fact in Camel 2.x the following snippet (defined in the documentation) doesn&apos;t work&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &amp;lt;route&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;from uri=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;timer:foo?repeatCount=1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;log message=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Before threads&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;threads poolSize=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;5&quot;&lt;/span&gt; /&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;log message=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;After threads&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if the new behavior is the right one or not. It&apos;s either a bug in 3.x or a missing information in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://camel.apache.org/manual/latest/camel-3-migration-guide.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;migration guide&lt;/a&gt; (searched from &quot;threads&quot; but couldn&apos;t find anything).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you have a look? Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
